From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: replace BT DIS LOG_INF with printk to isolate hang

Patch 0021 removed the QSPI flash deep-sleep block but main still
hangs at the SAME spot — between WR_TRACE 1_dcdc_done (visible) and
2_qspi_done (never appears). With the QSPI block gone, the only code
between those two checkpoints is:

    LOG_INF("Firmware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_FW_REV_STR);
    LOG_INF("Hardware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_HW_REV_STR);

CONFIG_BT was assigned 'y' but the BT_GATT_AUTO_UPDATE_MTU build
warning showed BT_HCI_HOST or BT_GATT_CLIENT may not be satisfied,
leaving the BT subsystem partially configured. CONFIG_BT_DIS_*_STR
macros may resolve to NULL or some half-defined symbol, and the
deferred-log machinery dereferences the %s arg either during arg
copy or in the log thread.

Swap to printk for these two lines and add fine-grained checkpoints
on either side, so we can see exactly which call hangs.

This is a debug patch; remove once the SD bring-up is solid.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -147,9 +147,11 @@ int main(void)
     printk("WR_TRACE: 1_dcdc_done\n");
     LOG_INF("Booting...\n");

-    LOG_INF("Model: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_MODEL);
-    LOG_INF("Firmware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_FW_REV_STR);
-    LOG_INF("Hardware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_HW_REV_STR);
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1a_pre_model\n");
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1b_model: %s\n", CONFIG_BT_DIS_MODEL);
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1c_fw: %s\n", CONFIG_BT_DIS_FW_REV_STR);
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1d_hw: %s\n", CONFIG_BT_DIS_HW_REV_STR);
+    printk("WR_TRACE: 1e_after_dis\n");
     /* patch 0021: skipped — pm_device_action_run hangs main when
      * SPI_NOR=n (deps unsatisfied in NCS v2.7). See patch header. */
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2_qspi_done\n");
